<h5>
Presentation 4: Motives to be vegetarian
</h5>
<p>
Authors: Christopher Hopwood &amp; Wiebke Bleidorn<br>
Speaker: Christopher Hopwood (University of California, Davis)</p>
<h5>Abstract</h5>
<p>
In this paper we will present work we have recently published in a series of
papers on the measurement of veg*n dietary motives. We will review the
development of the Vegetarian Eating Motives Inventory (VEMI), which
measures health, environmental, and animal rights motives for veg*n diet.
We will present evidence that the measurement model is invariant across
English and Dutch respondents and across vegetarian and non-vegetarian
respondents, review major correlates of each motive, and discuss the
importance of distinguishing among individual differences in motivation for
future work in animal rights advocacy.
</p>
